Early gains for Japanese, Antipodean stocks

2016-06-23

It’s early days, but for the Asian markets that are up and running, things are looking up on Brexit day.

About a quarter-of-an-hour into the trading day, Japan’s broad Topix is up 0.2 per cent, while the Nikkei 225 is ahead by 0.4 per cent. Materials is the best-performing sector for the Topix, while it’s consumer discretionary leading the Nikkei as index heavyweight Fast Retailing rises 2.2 per cent.

Australia’s S&P/ASX 200 is up 0.3 per cent, with materials the best-performing sector. New Zealand’s S&P/NZX 50 is also up 0.3 per cent.

All Asian currencies are up against the US dollar with the exception of the yen, which is 0.3 per cent weaker.

